data_table.description: The dataset provides information gathered following administration of various doses of d-amphetamine over 3 - 4 visits. Data of physiological responses, such as blood pressure, heart rate, and emotional status (determined using the Addiction Research Center, Drug Effects and Profile of Moods, inventory/questionnaires), as well as data of performance status in various tasks (i.e. Delay discounting Task, Go/No-Go Task, Stop Task) of healthy volunteer participants are reported. Basic anthropometric (height/weight/BMI) and sociodemographic (n= 11 variables) data are included.
